      <guid>https://qferbs.github.io/project/fan-controller/</guid>
      <description>













&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-the-full-fan-assembly-the-housing-was-3d-printed&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34; &gt;
        &lt;img alt=&#34;The full fan assembly. The housing was 3D printed.&#34; srcset=&#34;
               /project/fan-controller/window-fan_hu346252964163f473eabd60875f60b2f3_2381440_cd62b0f0c46aae835b49e740dc178feb.jpg 400w,
               /project/fan-controller/window-fan_hu346252964163f473eabd60875f60b2f3_2381440_bfbc8d49b4bdb3527aba53a8d825b496.jpg 760w,
               /project/fan-controller/window-fan_hu346252964163f473eabd60875f60b2f3_2381440_1200x1200_fit_q75_lanczos.jpg 1200w&#34;
               src=&#34;https://qferbs.github.io/project/fan-controller/window-fan_hu346252964163f473eabd60875f60b2f3_2381440_cd62b0f0c46aae835b49e740dc178feb.jpg&#34;
               width=&#34;760&#34;
               height=&#34;672&#34;
               loading=&#34;lazy&#34; data-zoomable /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      The full fan assembly. The housing was 3D printed.
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A window fan that uses a custom PCB running an ATMega chip to control the RPM of 3-pin PC case fans. The voltage across the fans is controlled by a buck converter built solely out of discrete components and controlled by a PID loop to accurately match a set RPM.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
